             (Police-constable K 66.) I was called in to take charge of the prisoner for stealing a pelisse and waistcoat - he said he meant to pawn them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to the box to get a clean waistcoat; there was a pelisse laid on the top, and as I was taking it out, my mother came in, and accused me of the robbery.</p>
